What you need to know:

Kenya was supposed to begin its second phase of vaccination in May but the government extended the process to 12 weeks after India banned the exportation of vaccines following the rise in Covid-19 cases in the countryWachuka was speaking during the National Olympic Committee of Kenya (NOC-K) Facebook-Live series webinar dubbed #TeamKenyaLive, moderated by sports journalist Robin ToskinKenya began vaccinating its population in March after getting one million doses of AstraZeneca vaccines from India